has the highest IQ for his age
in all of Europe.

273
00:44:48,690 --> 00:44:53,360
That little man there
is the human time-signal.

274
00:44:53,400 --> 00:44:59,740
It's his voice you hear
when you dial 463.84.00.

275
00:44:59,770 --> 00:45:04,180
But it's been downhill
for him ever since.

276
00:45:07,150 --> 00:45:10,600
That's Henri Bestouches,
artist and poet.

277
00:45:10,650 --> 00:45:15,350
He's very ill. He has a bullet
lodged in his brain.

278
00:45:17,960 --> 00:45:23,450
There's Mireille over there
with Elizabeth.

279
00:45:28,000 --> 00:45:31,160
The lady in the white sweater,
Josette Lemercier...

280
00:45:31,200 --> 00:45:36,040
was Miss Universe
in the late '50s.

281
00:45:36,080 --> 00:45:38,980
The handsome guy
near the window...

282
00:45:39,010 --> 00:45:40,240
is Jerry Bridgeman.

283
00:45:40,280 --> 00:45:44,220
A U.S. astronaut
who walked on the moon.

284
00:45:47,250 --> 00:45:48,810
Who are you?

285
00:45:50,790 --> 00:45:53,020
I'll be off, Alex.

286
00:46:15,510 --> 00:46:19,640
First came words.
No, emotions...

287
00:46:56,920 --> 00:46:59,020
Sorry. I don't understand.

288
00:47:08,130 --> 00:47:13,130
He says,
"Young people are too silent."

289
00:47:14,540 --> 00:47:17,130
"You've forgotten how to talk."

290
00:47:18,380 --> 00:47:23,370
"Maybe you think
people aren't worth talking to."

291
00:47:23,420 --> 00:47:24,940
That's not it.

292
00:47:31,390 --> 00:47:36,260
"You're wrong.
Maybe you're afraid."

293
00:47:38,260 --> 00:47:42,530
He wants to know
if you like movies.

294
00:47:42,570 --> 00:47:47,800
"I was a grip when movies
were as silent as I am."

295
00:47:53,050 --> 00:47:55,980
"I pushed the first dollies."

296
00:48:12,200 --> 00:48:16,790
"I remember that matinee idol,
Jonas."

297
00:48:18,970 --> 00:48:21,770
"He made the whole crew laugh.

298
00:48:21,810 --> 00:48:25,710
"Whenever they shot
a love scene...

299
00:48:25,740 --> 00:48:30,700
"the director
told the actors..."

300
00:48:32,020 --> 00:48:36,720
"to say tender words
to each other before kissing.

301
00:48:36,760 --> 00:48:41,220
"Anything, so one could see
their lips moving.

302
00:48:41,260 --> 00:48:47,060
"So in the middle
of a love scene, Jonas...

303
00:48:47,100 --> 00:48:53,060
"would make daring comments
on his partner's breasts...

304
00:48:53,110 --> 00:48:57,940
"or proposition her
during a take."

305
00:48:58,940 --> 00:49:03,070
"Jonas,
who was a gentle person...

306
00:49:03,120 --> 00:49:07,210
"and shy with women
in real life...

307
00:49:07,250 --> 00:49:13,320
"became a lion
in front of the camera."

308
00:49:22,070 --> 00:49:24,540
He says...

309
00:49:24,570 --> 00:49:26,900
"When the films were shown..."

310
00:49:29,510 --> 00:49:31,640
"during the love scenes...

311
00:49:31,680 --> 00:49:36,740
"one or two people
in the theater would laugh.

312
00:49:36,780 --> 00:49:38,980
"They were deaf people...

313
00:49:39,020 --> 00:49:43,960
"who could lip-read
Jonas' obscenities.

314
00:49:43,990 --> 00:49:48,150
"Silent films were better
because...because..."

315
00:49:48,190 --> 00:49:50,020
Slow down, Sylvain.

316
00:49:50,060 --> 00:49:51,590
Excuse me.

317
00:50:25,230 --> 00:50:27,820
Miss, I watched you all night.

318
00:50:27,870 --> 00:50:30,390
I composed this for you.

319
00:50:31,840 --> 00:50:33,830
I'll play it for you.

320
00:51:32,530 --> 00:51:35,860
We're too old to change
our habits.

321
00:52:36,600 --> 00:52:37,760
Shit!

322
00:52:50,010 --> 00:52:52,670
They say that broken glass...

323
00:53:01,150 --> 00:53:03,050
We should pick it up.

324
00:53:51,100 --> 00:53:52,800
What did he say?

325
00:53:52,840 --> 00:53:54,600
He said, "C'est la vie."

326
00:53:54,640 --> 00:53:57,010
That's what life's about.

327
00:54:03,950 --> 00:54:08,940
I was nine when you walked
your first steps.

328
00:54:08,990 --> 00:54:13,190
For years,
I lived only for outer space.

329
00:54:13,230 --> 00:54:18,220
But don't you think
it's hopelessly screwed up now?

330
00:54:41,320 --> 00:54:43,310
How old are you, Jenny?

331
00:54:43,360 --> 00:54:45,920
18. And you?

332
00:54:45,960 --> 00:54:50,360
I turned 53...recently.

333
00:54:51,560 --> 00:54:54,400
I'll be 28 on August 22nd.

334
00:54:56,700 --> 00:54:59,470
You know what distresses me?

335
00:54:59,500 --> 00:55:04,440
That I've accomplished
so little in my life.

336
00:55:04,480 --> 00:55:08,710
It's my 37th birthday today.

337
00:55:08,750 --> 00:55:11,770
37 goddamn years!

338
00:55:11,820 --> 00:55:15,840
Makes you stop and think.

339
00:55:20,630 --> 00:55:25,690
When Mozart was my age,
he had been dead for two years!

340
00:55:25,730 --> 00:55:28,170
How depressing!

341
00:55:28,200 --> 00:55:30,530
But there's a way out:

342
00:55:30,570 --> 00:55:32,400
blowing my brains out!

343
00:55:32,440 --> 00:55:36,340
-May I make a call?
-Come with me.

344
00:55:36,380 --> 00:55:38,100
Axel.

345
00:56:12,910 --> 00:56:16,510
Thomas? It's me.

346
00:56:16,550 --> 00:56:19,140
Recovered from your swim?

347
00:56:19,180 --> 00:56:21,520
Is that Florence I hear?

348
00:56:21,550 --> 00:56:25,960
There's a letter for both of you
under the door.

349
00:56:25,990 --> 00:56:29,430
The records in the bag
are for Florence.

350
00:56:29,460 --> 00:56:31,260
That's all. Ciao.

351
00:57:56,080 --> 00:57:58,140
Good night, Nicolas.

352
00:57:58,180 --> 00:58:02,240
Good night, Pimpernel.

353
00:58:02,290 --> 00:58:04,780
You know our names, Mr. Bear?

354
00:58:04,820 --> 00:58:06,420
Of course.

355
00:58:06,460 --> 00:58:10,590
Will you come play
with us tomorrow, Mr. Bear?

356
00:58:10,630 --> 00:58:13,890
Only if you go to bed right now!

357
00:58:18,200 --> 00:58:22,260
Good night,
Nicolas and Pimpernel.

358
00:58:22,310 --> 00:58:24,740
Good night
to all our little friends.

359
00:58:24,780 --> 00:58:27,270
Time for beddy-bye.

360
00:58:27,310 --> 00:58:29,370
Kiss your parents good night...

361
00:58:29,410 --> 00:58:32,650
and we'll be back
tomorrow night.

362
00:58:32,680 --> 00:58:34,310
Good night.

363
00:58:35,450 --> 00:58:37,550
See you tomorrow.

364
01:02:13,170 --> 01:02:15,900
You're just like Bernard
at a party:

365
01:02:15,940 --> 01:02:21,380
always in the kitchen, alone.

366
01:02:22,580 --> 01:02:24,780
I'll get you a glass.

367
01:02:30,160 --> 01:02:33,780
All the glasses
are in the living room.

368
01:02:36,460 --> 01:02:39,290
This cup is all that's left.

369
01:02:51,940 --> 01:02:54,500
My private cup.

370
01:02:54,550 --> 01:02:57,780
I'm the only one
who's ever drunk from it.

371
01:02:57,820 --> 01:03:04,810
Even my brother Stan
would never have used it.

372
01:03:04,860 --> 01:03:09,380
He bought it for me in ltaly.

373
01:03:09,430 --> 01:03:13,330
Stan traveled everywhere.

374
01:03:14,570 --> 01:03:20,060
Whenever we were apart,
even as children...

375
01:03:20,110 --> 01:03:24,300
we would meet through
telepathy at night.

376
01:03:24,340 --> 01:03:27,370
At exactly 10 p.m...

377
01:03:27,410 --> 01:03:30,640
I'd think very hard of Stan...

378
01:03:30,680 --> 01:03:34,780
and he'd think very hard of me.

379
01:03:36,590 --> 01:03:42,390
Three years ago, I forgot
my telepathic date with him.

380
01:03:45,630 --> 01:03:49,660
He was in Germany,
on a business trip.

381
01:03:52,100 --> 01:03:55,370
I never saw him again.

382
01:03:55,410 --> 01:04:00,710
He died on a German freeway...

383
01:04:00,750 --> 01:04:03,410
In his car...

384
01:04:03,450 --> 01:04:06,010
Totally dead!

385
01:04:11,660 --> 01:04:16,420
Be very careful with my cup...

386
01:04:16,460 --> 01:04:17,790
Alexander.

387
01:05:36,340 --> 01:05:39,040
Mireille?

388
01:05:39,080 --> 01:05:40,940
Your hair...

389
01:05:46,180 --> 01:05:48,680
Next time you do something
like that...

390
01:05:48,720 --> 01:05:52,320
please don't do it in my home.

391
01:05:52,360 --> 01:05:55,550
You did it behind
Bernard's back.

392
01:05:55,590 --> 01:05:57,080
He'll be furious.

393
01:05:59,200 --> 01:06:02,290
Bernard won't mind,
I assure you.

394
01:06:02,330 --> 01:06:04,530
Don't worry.

395
01:06:25,390 --> 01:06:27,450
You, too!

396
01:06:27,490 --> 01:06:31,760
Isn't it nice
to drink through the chink?

397
01:09:03,510 --> 01:09:05,680
I'm going to wind up a loser.

398
01:09:05,720 --> 01:09:08,550
Yet I stood a chance.

399
01:09:08,590 --> 01:09:11,210
I wanted to be someone
outstanding:

400
01:09:11,260 --> 01:09:14,420
flyer, traveler, musician...

401
01:09:17,060 --> 01:09:19,430
Can't I be reborn?

402
01:09:23,370 --> 01:09:26,800
I'm going to wind up a loser.
Yet I stood a chance.

403
01:09:26,840 --> 01:09:28,770
I wanted to be
someone outstanding:

404
01:09:28,810 --> 01:09:32,110
flyer, traveler, musician...

405
01:09:32,140 --> 01:09:34,740
Can't I be reborn?

406
01:10:01,070 --> 01:10:03,470
It's our first meeting.

407
01:10:04,510 --> 01:10:07,970
Only first times matter to me.

408
01:10:08,010 --> 01:10:11,210
Then you won't last long.

409
01:10:11,250 --> 01:10:14,180
If I had a kid,
I'd ignore him once he talked.

410
01:10:14,220 --> 01:10:16,350
For years,
I longed to make love.

411
01:10:16,390 --> 01:10:18,510
Then I actually did it.
I mean...

412
01:10:18,560 --> 01:10:20,320
No, it's the opposite.

413
01:10:20,360 --> 01:10:26,130
I never tried to fulfill my best
dreams. Only to re-dream them.

414
01:10:27,500 --> 01:10:28,930
Want some tea?

415
01:10:28,970 --> 01:10:30,090
Sure.

416
01:10:30,130 --> 01:10:32,230
There's only one cup.

417
01:10:39,540 --> 01:10:41,540
The label's been cut off.

418
01:10:41,580 --> 01:10:44,880
It could be anything.

419
01:11:00,100 --> 01:11:03,400
I saw you in the bathroom
earlier.

420
01:11:03,430 --> 01:11:05,400
Quite a scene.

421
01:11:06,940 --> 01:11:10,270
So you're the spy.

422
01:11:10,310 --> 01:11:13,180
I've tried it more often
since I came to Paris.

423
01:11:14,350 --> 01:11:16,040
Haven't you ever?

424
01:11:16,080 --> 01:11:18,240
I'm too happy for that.

425
01:11:18,280 --> 01:11:19,480
Too happy?

426
01:11:19,520 --> 01:11:22,350
Yes. I mean, too scared.

427
01:11:23,920 --> 01:11:26,050
Where are you from?

428
01:11:26,090 --> 01:11:29,820
Blois. In the Loire Valley.

429
01:11:29,860 --> 01:11:35,030
I came here a year ago to live
with my friend, a Parisian.

430
01:11:35,070 --> 01:11:38,830
I wanted to act in commercials,
but I got nowhere.

431
01:11:38,870 --> 01:11:42,530
I almost got hired
by a chocolate firm...

432
01:11:42,570 --> 01:11:45,540
but then they saw my tooth...

433
01:11:45,580 --> 01:11:48,640
Next, it was a cosmetics firm...

434
01:11:48,680 --> 01:11:50,340
but with my wrinkles...

435
01:11:50,380 --> 01:11:51,810
What wrinkles?

436
01:11:51,850 --> 01:11:53,370
On my forehead.

437
01:11:53,420 --> 01:11:54,650
I see.

438
01:11:55,720 --> 01:11:59,620
Five of them.
I've had them since childhood.

439
01:11:59,660 --> 01:12:02,290
I make films.

440
01:12:02,330 --> 01:12:04,620
Films or video?

441
01:12:05,730 --> 01:12:08,160
For now,
what I do is dream up titles...

442
01:12:08,200 --> 01:12:09,860
for the films I plan to make.

443
01:12:09,900 --> 01:12:12,390
If I were you...

444
01:12:14,440 --> 01:12:17,670
I have to go into the army
tomorrow.

445
01:12:17,710 --> 01:12:19,640
If I were you, I wouldn't go!

446
01:12:19,680 --> 01:12:23,140
Right. Why go,
when we're already veterans?

447
01:12:23,180 --> 01:12:25,170
It's menopause time.

448
01:12:25,220 --> 01:12:27,150
And I'm in a rush.

449
01:12:27,180 --> 01:12:30,810
Yet I'm all for conquerors.

450
01:12:30,860 --> 01:12:35,160
I had a great line worked out
for the army psychiatrists.

451
01:12:35,190 --> 01:12:37,390
I told them
I was unfit for service...

452
01:12:37,430 --> 01:12:41,730
because I couldn't sleep
in a room with other guys.

453
01:12:41,770 --> 01:12:43,760
It didn't work.

454
01:12:43,800 --> 01:12:48,200
They said the army wasn't for
sleeping. So I'm off tomorrow.

455
01:12:50,740 --> 01:12:52,830
Do you fall...

456
01:12:52,880 --> 01:12:55,740
Do you fall in love often?

457
01:12:55,780 --> 01:12:57,840
Yes, easily.

458
01:12:57,880 --> 01:13:00,480
I thought so.

459
01:13:00,520 --> 01:13:03,180
But a real lover sticks around.

460
01:13:03,220 --> 01:13:06,020
I feel closer
to people once I've left.

461
01:13:06,060 --> 01:13:08,360
Love is as old as the hills...

462
01:13:08,390 --> 01:13:10,290
Lovers are worn out.

463
01:13:10,330 --> 01:13:12,450
Desire isn't easy to come by...

464
01:13:12,500 --> 01:13:15,020
and it doesn't come cheap
nowadays.

465
01:13:15,070 --> 01:13:19,060
There's plenty of passion,
but it gets wasted on details.

466
01:13:19,100 --> 01:13:22,660
And it doesn't travel.
Me, neither.

467
01:13:24,610 --> 01:13:25,940
Mireille...

468
01:13:27,750 --> 01:13:29,980
I'm going now.

469
01:13:30,010 --> 01:13:31,500
OK.

470
01:13:44,560 --> 01:13:47,730
Who are you in love with
these days?

471
01:13:48,900 --> 01:13:51,230
I'm on to a new heartbreak.

472
01:13:51,270 --> 01:13:53,000
I don't want to lose it.

473
01:13:53,040 --> 01:13:56,500
My heart's proud of its pain.

474
01:13:56,540 --> 01:13:58,300
Her name is Florence.

475
01:13:58,340 --> 01:14:03,910
I met her two years ago, but I
toyed with her before that.

476
01:14:03,950 --> 01:14:07,650
Now she's left me
for my best friend, Thomas.

477
01:14:07,690 --> 01:14:09,620
Same old story.

478
01:14:09,650 --> 01:14:12,420
I've never cheated on anyone.

479
01:14:12,460 --> 01:14:15,450
Never got the chance.

480
01:14:15,490 --> 01:14:16,890
She's gone.

481
01:14:16,930 --> 01:14:19,160
She left me a note
in our toothglass:

482
01:14:19,200 --> 01:14:22,630
"I'm leaving to forget you."

483
01:14:22,670 --> 01:14:25,360
In her deadly prose.

484
01:14:26,370 --> 01:14:28,740
We lived in my room.

485
01:14:28,770 --> 01:14:31,640
We slept in my single bed.

486
01:14:31,680 --> 01:14:34,080
And lived on her unemployment.

487
01:14:34,110 --> 01:14:36,240
Yet she still loved me
on Sunday...

488
01:14:36,280 --> 01:14:38,750
Even Monday...and Tuesday...

489
01:14:40,120 --> 01:14:44,490
She told me all about her youth.
She had lots of love affairs.

490
01:14:44,520 --> 01:14:47,320
One when she was very young
with a boy who died.

491
01:14:47,360 --> 01:14:50,290
His death nearly destroyed her.

492
01:14:50,330 --> 01:14:53,060
I never got along with her...

493
01:14:53,100 --> 01:14:55,660
Last summer,
we were on an Aeolian island.

494
01:14:55,700 --> 01:14:57,690
I gave her my first slap.

495
01:14:57,740 --> 01:15:01,030
I could've held back,
but I decided not to.

496
01:15:01,070 --> 01:15:03,630
I don't try to change.
She didn't get it...

497
01:15:03,670 --> 01:15:07,580
that I kept tabs on my
cowardice, on my weaknesses.

498
01:15:07,610 --> 01:15:12,170
I like to spy on myself
as if I were a foreigner...

499
01:15:12,220 --> 01:15:14,710
a foreign body,
as scientists say.

500
01:15:14,750 --> 01:15:18,020
If I changed,
I'd distort the experiment.

501
01:15:19,390 --> 01:15:22,120
I can see the kind of movies
you'll make.

502
01:15:22,160 --> 01:15:25,250
It's easy to get self-obsessed
when you're alone.

503
01:15:25,300 --> 01:15:29,430
I've got lots of projects,
enough for two lives.

504
01:15:29,470 --> 01:15:32,630
I like to view my life
as a biography.

505
01:15:32,670 --> 01:15:38,070
Born in Paris 1960. Died
in Paris 2040. I won't leave.

506
01:15:38,110 --> 01:15:40,080
Last week I had a dream.

507
01:15:40,110 --> 01:15:43,410
In my dream, I was asleep,
then I was awake...

508
01:15:43,450 --> 01:15:46,750
and found a book between
the sheet and the blanket...

509
01:15:46,780 --> 01:15:48,680
a book I'd never seen before.

510
01:15:48,720 --> 01:15:52,450
I leafed through it.
It was my autobiography.

511
01:15:52,490 --> 01:15:56,150
But it was unfinished.
I'd died while writing it.

512
01:16:19,250 --> 01:16:21,680
-Want some?
-I don't drink.

513
01:16:30,330 --> 01:16:34,560
Florence was madly
in love with me.

514
01:16:34,600 --> 01:16:36,930
More than I with her.

515
01:16:36,970 --> 01:16:40,660
So now she's down, and I'm out!

516
01:16:40,700 --> 01:16:43,730
When she left three days ago,
we had a...

517
01:16:46,880 --> 01:16:48,500
She took all her things.

518
01:16:48,550 --> 01:16:51,510
She wanted to take the letters
I wrote her.

519
01:16:51,550 --> 01:16:53,210
I said they were mine.

520
01:16:53,250 --> 01:16:56,280
I wrote them. They're mine.

521
01:16:56,320 --> 01:16:58,950
In the end, I gave in.

522
01:16:58,990 --> 01:17:02,930
She doesn't know
I've Xeroxed them.

523
01:17:08,330 --> 01:17:11,790
This scarf
is all I have left of her.

524
01:17:12,900 --> 01:17:16,270
But...it's her all over.

525
01:17:20,780 --> 01:17:22,680
You really think so, Mireille?

526
01:17:25,480 --> 01:17:27,540
You know my name?

527
01:17:28,690 --> 01:17:32,350
In the army, they should
assign you to espionage.

528
01:17:49,570 --> 01:17:52,040
-Want one?
-I don't smoke.

529
01:17:58,950 --> 01:18:02,150
I'm going out for a walk.

530
01:18:04,690 --> 01:18:06,850
I'll come with you.

531
01:18:06,890 --> 01:18:08,950
I like walking alone.

532
01:18:08,990 --> 01:18:10,150
So do I.

533
01:18:10,190 --> 01:18:12,860
Then we can go together.

534
01:18:12,900 --> 01:18:15,420
In fact, I don't go out much.

